id="post-4214" class="post-4214 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-music-art tag-sohn"><h2 class="entry-title"><a
href="http://www.thingsaregood.com/2014/04/18/band-of-the-month-sohn/" title="Permalink to Band of the Month: SOHN" rel="bookmark">Band of the Month: SOHN</a></h2><div
class="entry-meta"> <span
class="entry-date" title="2014/04/18 9:00 am"><a
href="http://www.thingsaregood.com/2014/04/18/band-of-the-month-sohn/" title="Band of the Month: SOHN" rel="bookmark">2014/04/18 9:00 am</a></span><span
class="entry-meta-sep"> / </span><span
class="comments-link"><a
href="http://www.thingsaregood.com/2014/04/18/band-of-the-month-sohn/#comments">Leave a Comment</a></span><span
class="entry-meta-sep"> / </span><span
class="entry-author author vcard"><a
href="http://www.thingsaregood.com/author/greg/" title="by Greg" rel="author">Greg</a></span></div><div
class="entry-content clearfix"><p>Hey readers!</p><p>This months band is <a
href="http://sohnmusic.com/">SOHN</a>.</p><p>London born and Vienna settled, SOHN is longing, brooding, and beautiful. Much like Toronto&#8217;s current state of anticipation for this winter&#8217;s eventual end. <a
href="https://soundcloud.com/sohnmusic">SOHN</a> uses powerfully pulsing digital beats with spiralling layers of arpeggiating synth to provide an appropriately intense foundation for the mezmorzing, high tenor vocal harmonies.</p><p>Crank it while you look out your window and dream of the oncoming Spring.</p><p><iframe
width="640" height="360" src="//www.youtube.com/embed/9btsq496hkQ?feature=player_detailpage" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p><a
href="https://www.facebook.com/thebenefitofthefreeman">Greg O&#8217;Toole</a></p><div
