class="entry-meta"> <span
class="entry-date" title="2014/04/14 10:35 am"><a
href="http://www.thingsaregood.com/2014/04/14/ducks-a-story-about-the-tar-sands/" title="Ducks: A Story About the Tar Sands" rel="bookmark">2014/04/14 10:35 am</a></span><span
class="entry-meta-sep"> / </span><span
class="comments-link"><a
href="http://www.thingsaregood.com/2014/04/14/ducks-a-story-about-the-tar-sands/#comments">Leave a Comment</a></span><span
class="entry-meta-sep"> / </span><span
class="entry-author author vcard"><a
href="http://www.thingsaregood.com/author/administrator/" title="by Adam Clare" rel="author">Adam Clare</a></span></div><div
class="entry-content clearfix"><p>Kate Beaton of <a
href="http://www.harkavagrant.com/index.php">Hark a Vagrant</a> fame once worked in the Alberta tar sands. She recently made a short comic about her time working there (which she did to pay off student debt) and it provides a wonderful human side to the tar sands narrative.</p><p><a
